Why Decorators?
DRY Principle — write cross-cutting concerns once
Separation of concerns — keep core logic clean
Reusable — apply same behavior to many functions
Non-invasive — add behavior without changing original
Common uses:
Logging, timing, caching
Authentication, authorization
Input validation
Retry logic
Rate limiting
